We hiked this trail to Pico Ruivo planning to see the sunset, and we arrived just in time as the sun was setting behind the mountains ‚õ∞. To be honest, we had to rush a bit at the end because the beauty of this hike is one that makes you stop every 5 minutes for a picture or just to stare at the amazing landscape. 
We marveled at the sunset, met some people on the top that were preparing to sleep under the stars, relaxed for a while, and as the night came, we started our walk back to the car. The sky was fully covered with stars ‚ú®, there was a cold breeze, and we were a bit afraid as we were alone in the dark. It was one of the most memorable experiences of my life, and certainly one of the most beautiful hikes I‚Äôve ever made.
